{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And after that, I was not so afraid anymore to go down to the root cellar, because I was always-- my mother-- the echo of my mother's voice was still in my head. 'Go, go, Itkele.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "God is in the root cellar.' In fact, during concentration camp, I was often thinking about this comment.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I was thinking, when I was in Poland, we didn't have electricity.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But neither did we have electric charge wires when we were fenced in and couldn't go out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So-- and then, also, there was, for instance, Passover I remember very much.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "For one thing, I was born during Passover, you know, the Jewish holiday celebrating freedom.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I remember Passover was very beautiful in our home, because we had a large-- lots of relatives.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "My aunt and uncle had seven children, and they had already grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the relatives would used to go together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But what I remember most is that it was completely because of the inconveniences of lacking the things, which I said, the modern things, my mother and grandmother-- may they rest in peace-- used to buy beets.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And before the, before the holiday, so like a month before, make beets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Buy raisin, make their own raisin wine, because it was strictly kosher in our home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Prepare.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we used to go, you know, in a, in a pillow case we would put in and go bring the matza-- a special pillow case.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was not a pillow case that you slept, but, like, it looked like a pillow case.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Bring home the matza for, for yuntif.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And at the seder, I used to love the way they did the seder.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And-- but to tell you the truth, if every year we prayed, next year in Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But the point is, to me, it was like a story.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I believed it, but I, I was still fortunate that I still had a family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I never knew what hunger was, because I wasn't 13 years-- I was 13 when the war started.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So till 13, I didn't fast for Yom Kippur, so I didn't know what hunger is, you know, because I haven't experienced it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a story with all the plagues, with all the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So till-- and later on, I was thinking, when I was-- during the Holocaust, realizing that now I know it's not just a story.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now I experienced far worse than what it was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Another thing which I loved that my parents used to take me to the Yiddish theater.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I mentioned before, my mother would only give a performance occasionally.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What type?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Yiddish theater.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember that we went to-- the play that I'm telling now, I didn't see her perform in that play.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they took me much to the theater.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was, as far as I remember, it was not even a real theater.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was in the house where the firemen had, you know, their house, they used to allow them to make performances.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I remember that I saw many, many Yiddish shows, like Ansky's And in fact, I was telling my children about the story, because there was a scene that stuck in my mind, in particular, that when one, one who is in that play, calls over the man because-- and says to him, 'Look through the window.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What do you see?' And he said, 'People.' 'Look in the mirror.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What do you see?' He says, 'Myself.' He said, 'It's the same piece of glass.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But as soon as there is a little silver on it, you only see yourself.'",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was in reference, because the story was about two friends who started in the yeshiva together, and they pledged-- both wives were pregnant-- that if one has a daughter and one a son, that they're going to be, going to marry each other.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In our tradition, we don't, not allowed to make promises like this, because you cannot make a promise on something that is not born.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's like, you know, like, well, I have a saying. 'The past is history, the present is news, and the future is still unborn.' So you don't give such promises.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it so happened that one has a son and one a daughter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "However, the one who had the daughter became extremely rich, and he didn't keep his promise.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He completely forgot the promise.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the whole tragedy comes [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I'm not going to go into the whole play.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was a play by, by Ansky's that I played.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I told it to my children, and they went to see it, they said, 'Mom, you were a little girl.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
